# PRD-000001
# Product Vision & Product Definition

Version: 1.0
Status: Draft
Owner: CTO
Project: Hades AI Growth OS

---

# 1. Vision

Hades AI Growth OS is an internal AI-native operating system designed to automate digital growth.

Instead of providing isolated SEO tools, Hades coordinates AI reasoning, AI agents and execution engines to continuously improve website growth with minimal human intervention.

The long-term vision is:

One Mission.
One Command.
AI Executes Everything.

---

# 2. Product Position

Hades is NOT:

- A traditional SEO tool
- A keyword research platform
- A CMS
- A website builder
- A SaaS marketing platform

Hades IS:

An AI Growth Operating System.

SEO is only one Engine.

GEO is only one Engine.

Content is only one Engine.

Publishing is only one Engine.

Everything belongs to one operating system.

---

# 3. Product Scope (V1)

Version 1 is designed for internal team use only.

Characteristics:

- Internal deployment
- Chinese management console
- Global-ready architecture
- English codebase
- English database schema
- English API
- Multi-language content capability
- Multi-country capability

Not included in V1:

- Multi-tenancy
- Billing
- Public registration
- Marketplace
- SaaS subscriptions

---

# 4. Core Philosophy

Traditional software requires people to operate functions.

Hades requires people to define objectives.

The AI determines execution.

---

# 5. Mission-Driven Architecture

Everything inside Hades starts with a Mission.

Example:

Mission:
Increase US organic traffic by 30%.

The system automatically:

- Research competitors
- Discover keywords
- Build content plans
- Generate articles
- Publish content
- Create internal links
- Monitor rankings
- Optimize continuously

Users manage Missions.

AI manages execution.

---

# 6. Core Components

The operating system consists of three major layers.

Brain

Responsible for planning, reasoning and decision making.

Agents

Responsible for executing intelligent tasks.

Engines

Responsible for completing specific business capabilities.

Examples:

SEO Engine

Content Engine

Crawler Engine

Ranking Engine

Publishing Engine

Analytics Engine

Future engines may be added without changing the architecture.

---

# 7. User Role

Version 1 contains one user role.

Administrator

Responsibilities:

Create Missions

Configure websites

Monitor execution

Approve AI decisions when necessary

Future versions may introduce additional roles.

---

# 8. Design Principles

Documentation First

Architecture First

AI Native

Mission Driven

Plugin First

Automation First

Global Ready

Chinese Console

English Development

Minimal Human Operations

---

# 9. Success Criteria

A successful Hades deployment enables a website to operate growth activities with minimal manual work.

Human responsibilities:

- Define business objectives
- Review critical decisions
- Monitor overall performance

AI responsibilities:

- Planning
- Scheduling
- Content generation
- SEO optimization
- Publishing
- Analysis
- Continuous improvement

---

# 10. Future Vision

The long-term objective is to create an operating system where digital growth becomes autonomous.

The user no longer manages SEO.

The user manages business goals.

Everything else is executed by AI.
